PIZZAFOOL - Mr. T's Pizza Ordering System
==========================================

A parody of Sun Microsystems' PizzaTool, where Mr. T from the
A-Team judges your pizza topping choices with varying degrees
of disapproval.

Built for Solaris 7 / CDE / Motif on real SPARC hardware.

Features:
  - 12 toppings with unique Mr. T reactions
  - 4 pizza sizes (Fool-size through A-Team size)  
  - 12 unique 256-color Mr. T cartoon images
  - Custom XPM file loader (no libXpm needed!)
  - Order summary with Mr. T commentary

Requirements:
  - Solaris 7 (or compatible) with CDE/Motif
  - GCC (tgcware gcc47 or similar) or Sun Workshop cc
  - X11 display (8-bit PseudoColor or better)

Build:
  make

Run:
  make run
  
  Or manually:
  DISPLAY=:0 PIZZAFOOL_IMAGES=./images ./pizzafool

The PIZZAFOOL_IMAGES environment variable tells PizzaFool where
to find the Mr. T XPM image files. If not set, it looks for an
"images" directory next to the binary.

Files:
  pizzafool.c     - Main source (includes built-in XPM parser)
  Makefile        - Build for Solaris 7 / SPARC
  images/         - 12 Mr. T cartoon poses in 256-color XPM format
    mrt_point1.xpm    - Pointing at viewer
    mrt_point2.xpm    - Pointing variant
    mrt_point3.xpm    - Pointing variant
    mrt_point4.xpm    - Pointing variant
    mrt_thumbsup1.xpm - Thumbs up (approval)
    mrt_thumbsup2.xpm - Thumbs up variant
    mrt_thumbsup3.xpm - Thumbs up variant
    mrt_angry1.xpm    - Angry fist
    mrt_angry2.xpm    - Angry variant
    mrt_crossed1.xpm  - Arms crossed (stern)
    mrt_happy1.xpm    - Happy smiling
    mrt_happy2.xpm    - Happy variant

"I pity the fool who puts pineapple on pizza!" - Mr. T
